        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "When a bank valuation comes in below the contract price in Brisbane, the buyer faces a valuation shortfall: the gap between what the bank will lend against and what they agreed to pay. If the contract is still conditional on finance, the buyer may have grounds to terminate or renegotiate. If the contract is already unconditional, the buyer is committed regardless of the shortfall and must fund the difference from their own savings."
