        "text": "Not if the contract is unconditional. Once a Brisbane property contract becomes unconditional, the buyer is legally committed to settle at the contract price regardless of what a bank valuation says. However, if the contract is still conditional on finance, a low valuation can give the buyer grounds to terminate under the finance condition, which may push the seller into a renegotiation to retain the buyer."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How can Brisbane sellers reduce the risk of a low valuation killing the deal?",
